"The lives of President Raisi and Foreign Minister Amirabdollahian are at risk > following the helicopter crash," said an Iranian official at Reuters, adding: "We are still confident, but the information from the place of the accident is very worrying." Twenty rescue teams are at work to find the helicopter. The research, said Interior Minister Ahmed Vahidi on state television, is very difficult because of the "favourable weather conditions", and in particular a thick fog. "It could take time to reach the area," he added, although it is believed that the place is in the forest of Dizmar, near the town of Varzaghan.&nbsp; A helicopter that had to look for the crash site was forced to go back.
