The Iranian Supreme Guide, the Aytollah Ali Khamenei>, held an urgent meeting with the country's Security Council after the incident news.&nbsp; The official agency Irna, which mentions the spokesman of the government Ali Bahadri Jahormi, writes that after the emergency meeting of the government council in Tehran, the executive vice president and some members of the Iranian government left for Tabriz, near the place where the apparatus with on board the president would end his flight.
&nbsp;
"We hope that God will bring back the honorable president and his companions in the arms of the nation. Everyone should pray for the health of this group of servants. If the Iranian people do not care, there will be no interruptions in the work of the country," said Khamenei during a meeting with the Pasdaran families.

